===Etymology 1===
From Old (and modern) French ''[[#French|prune]]'', from Latin ''[[prunum]]'', from Greek [[προυνον]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# ''(obsolete)'' A [[plum]].
# The dried, wrinkled fruit of certain species of [[plum]].

